// Journal strings

//Quest start
@12000 = ~The Perfect Poison

In the Slums of Athkatla, an Eldathyn named Merethan approached me about an incurable toxin spreading through the lands. He believes a shadowy poison supplier is behind it and asked for my help to trace the source.~

@12001 = ~The Perfect Poison

Merethan pointed me to Skann Delth, a small-time poison peddler who loiters on the Copper Coronet’s rooftop. I’m to press him for the origin of his deadliest wares. Merethan is waiting for me at the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums of Athkatla.~

@12002 = ~The Perfect Poison

I confronted Skann Delth and obtained a map to a secluded site called Toadstool Hollow. I must bring this map to Merethan, who awaits me at the Temple of Ilmater in the slums of Athkatla.~

@12003 = ~The Perfect Poison

Merethan wishes me to accompany him to Toadstool Hollow to see whether the poisoner will reveal himself. He awaits me at the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums so that we may depart together.~

@12004 = ~The Perfect Poison

At Toadstool Hollow, a supposed exchange turned into an ambush. The mysterious poisoner’s servant struck down Merethan, yet one of the arrows remained laced with the toxin. Before passing, he entrusted the arrow to me and urged that it be taken to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, Eldath's sanctuary.~

@12005 = ~The Perfect Poison

Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes that the key to understanding the poison lies within the ruins of an ancient elven city. He suspects the rare plant used to create it may grow there. To narrow our search, he has asked me to visit the Temple of Oghma in Athkatla and consult their tomes on the lost kingdom of Keltormir.~

@12006 = ~The Perfect Poison

I returned the tome from the Temple of Oghma to Fallskeeper Alatoasz. Its passages point to Myth Unnohyr: a ruined elven city whose shattered mythal breeds wild magic by day and dead magic by night. The taint has seeped into a rare plant used to craft the incurable poison. He marked the ruins on my map. I must travel to Myth Unnohyr, find the poisoner—a Malagent of Talona—and bring back a blossom of the corrupted plant so the Fallskeeper can attempt an antidote.~

@12007 = ~The Perfect Poison

I confronted the Malagent deep within the ruins of Myth Unnohyr. He confessed to fusing corrupt mythal magic into a novel toxin and boasted that multiple batches had already been distributed across Amn. He vowed to turn Myth Unnohyr into his lady’s toxic domain—but I put an end to his schemes. I must now bring a sample of the corrupted plant back to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell so that an antidote can be created.~

@12008 = ~The Perfect Poison

I have found the corrupted plant known as Groveglove—the source of the perfect poison. After defeating the Malagent, I must bring this sample to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, so he can attempt to cleanse its essence and brew an antidote.~

@12009 = ~The Perfect Poison

The Malagent is dead, and his vile work lies in ruins. I brought the Groveglove plant to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell, who believes an antidote can be created to counter the poison already spread across Amn. Yet to purify the tainted flower and craft the cure, further aid from other faiths will be required.~

// The antidote

@12100 = ~The Antidote

Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes the Groveglove flower can be cleansed and turned into an antidote. To succeed, the flower must be blessed three times—with the divine aspects of Life, Compassion, and Renewal. Alatoasz has granted me the first blessing himself, but I must seek out the other two.~

@12101 = ~The Antidote: Ilmater's Blessing of Compassion

I am to travel to the Temple of Ilmater in the Slums of Athkatla and request the Blessing of Compassion. The Fallskeeper believes the Ilmateri will aid our cause without hesitation.~

@12102 = ~The Antidote: Lathander's Blessing of Renewal

I must visit the Church of Lathander in Athkatla to receive the Blessing of Renewal.~

@12103 = ~The Antidote: Eldath’s singing water

Alatoasz has instructed me to collect a carafe of Eldath’s singing water from the grotto in Duskwood Dell. One of the handmaidens tending the sacred pool will provide it. The water will serve as the final medium through which the blessings must be combined.~

@12104 = ~The Antidote: Ilmater's Blessing of Compassion

I have received the Blessing of Compassion from the Ilmateri in the Slums. Their prayer imbued the Groveglove with a faint warmth—as if the flower itself responded to mercy.~

@12105 = ~The Antidote: Lathander's Blessing of Renewal

The priests of Lathander have bestowed the Blessing of Renewal. Bathed in sunlight, the Groveglove seemed to stir, its dark hue paling ever so slightly under the Morninglord’s grace.~

@12106 = ~The Antidote: Eldath’s singing water

I have obtained a jug of Eldath’s singing water from the grotto in Duskwood Dell. Its surface hums softly, reflecting every breath of the forest. Now all that remains is to return to Fallskeeper Alatoasz with the blessed flower and the sacred water.~

@12107 = ~The Antidote

All three blessings have been gathered—Life, Compassion, and Renewal—and I have secured Eldath’s singing water. I must now return to Fallskeeper Alatoasz in Duskwood Dell so that the antidote can finally be created and the corruption of the Groveglove purged once and for all.~

@12108 = ~The Antidote

I have gathered all that was required: the Groveglove flower, the blessings, and a carafe of Eldath’s singing water. Fallskeeper Alatoasz believes that to forge the antidote, the sanctified flower and the sacred water must be placed within the Malagent’s cauldron in the ruins of Myth Unnohyr—the very place where the poison was first brewed.~

@12110 = ~The Antidote

The ritual succeeded. From the Malagent’s corrupted cauldron rose a monstrous Poison Incarnation—an embodiment of the toxin’s final wrath. I destroyed it, and the Groveglove’s corruption was purged. The antidote has taken shape, shimmering with a calm, emerald light. I must bring it back to Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim in Duskwood Dell.~

@12111 = ~The Antidote

Fallskeeper Alatoasz has received the antidote and completed the ritual of purification. The venom that once threatened Amn and beyond can no longer spread. Peace returns to the waters, and the shadow of the poison has lifted.~

// chapter 6 Quest
@12200 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

An Eldathyn messenger found me near Suldanessellar. He bears news from Duskwood Dell and asked me to meet Fallskeeper Alatoasz Berendim there regarding new troubles in Myth Unnohyr. The messenger said the matter is not yet urgent, but I should visit Duskwood Dell and hear the Fallskeeper’s request when I can.~

@12202 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

In Duskwood Dell I was introduced to the ranger Mismal Al’Visalle. He and the Fallskeeper fear that Myth Unnohyr has worsened since my last battle there. Mismal believes an ancient undead evil he named 'wyrd' has possessed the corpse of the former elven commander and is feeding on Myth Unnohyr’s broken magic. If left unchecked, its undead will spill into the surrounding lands. Mismal will lead me to Myth Unnohyr.~

@12207 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I entered Myth Unnohyr. The way back was sealed by tangled growth—my only path runs forward through the heart of the ruins. Mismal will scout ahead; we are to meet beyond the tower.~

@12208 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

The wyrd manifested first as an undead wearing Elv-Esster’s face. It killed Mismal and tightened its hold over the city. There will be no retreat.~

@12209 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I confronted the wyrd. It boasted of ancient hunger and of binding itself to the city. The battle is joined. Wounded, the wyrd admitted that symbiotes anchor its power to Myth Unnohyr. If I destroy these nodes, I can weaken it.~

@12211 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I destroyed the symbiotes. An elven spirit bade me meet him beneath Mythrien’s temple; he claims to know how to end the wyrd.~

@12212 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

In the crypts below, I met the elven spirit again. He urged me to find the Green Rose of Mythrien and bear it to the temple’s heart to call upon the god’s aid. I should be able to find the rose among the ones still blooming in Myth Unnohyr.~

@12213 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I found the Green Rose of Mythrien. With it, I can attempt the summoning at Mythrien's old temple.~

@12214 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I summoned Mythrien Sarath. He cannot mend the Mythal in full, but he will sever the currents that feed the wyrd so I may face it on more equal ground. Mythrien has stilled the worst excess of the broken weave: the wyrd can no longer draw strength from the city’s wound. I must hunt it down and end it.~

@12216 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

The wyrd is defeated. Its hunger is silenced and Myth Unnohyr—at last—can breathe. I should speak to Mythrien again.~

@12217 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I have informed Mythrien of the wyrd’s destruction. As thanks he returned the Green Rose, now bearing a ward against hostile sorcery. He cannot restore the Mythal, but he has steadied it for a single year; during that time no corruption shall rise to feed upon it.~

@12218 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

An elven spirit thanked me: the silence is lifted, and Myth Unnohyr’s name may be spoken with pride once more.~

@12219 = ~Undead in Myth Unnohyr

I returned to Duskwood Dell. Fallskeeper Alatoasz received the news and rewarded my efforts. With divine aid, Myth Unnohyr will know a year of quiet.~

/******************************
SIDE quest journal entries
******************************/
// Duskwood Dell – Missing Faerie Twins Quest

@13000 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

The faeries of Duskwood Dell are missing. Brother Edrim has asked me to look into their disappearance. The twins were last seen speaking with a merchant dressed in bright red silk. The merchant continued west, toward Athkatla. He may be hiding among the traders of Waukeen’s Promenade. If he truly traffics in magical curiosities, someone there will have noticed him.~

@13001 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

Among the stalls of Waukeen’s Promenade, I have encountered a curious merchant who fits Brother Edrim’s description — a man in red silk, dealing in peculiar items and speaking with a strange, almost hypnotic charm. Something about him feels... wrong.~

@13002 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

The merchant calling himself Zar’khaan is no merchant at all, but a Rakshasa in disguise. I must find out if he carries the Dell-Light Twins with him — perhaps sealed within some kind of small vessel or enchanted trinket.~


@13003 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

I have found the Dell-Light Twins. The Rakshasa imprisoned them within a magical vessel sealed by powerful enchantment. Though the faeries seem unharmed, the jar refuses to open. I should return it to Brother Edrim in Duskwood Dell — perhaps he will know how to break the seal.~


@13004 = ~The Missing Faerie Twins

I have brought the faerie glass back to Brother Edrim in Duskwood Dell. He was able to brake the seal, and the Dell-Light Twins have emerged unharmed. Their laughter once again dances through Duskwood Dell. Peace — and some mischief — have returned to this quiet corner of the world.~






















